'''Phong Nha-Ke Bang''' (Vietnamese: ''Vườn quốc gia Phong Nha-Kẻ Bàng'') is a national park in [[Quang Binh Lalawigan]], [[Vietnam]]. This park has 300 caves and grottoes with a total length of 70 km, of which British and Vietnamese scientists have so far surveyed 20 km. This park has many underground rivers and has biological diversity. In 2003, [[UNESCO]] listed this national park in its world heritage sites (natural heritage sites).
